-- Knicks Season Tickets to Rise 6.4%, Rangers by 4% on Average
-- B y   S c o t t   S o s h n i c k
-- 2013-03-11T19:45:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-11/knicks-season-tickets-to-rise-6-4-rangers-by-4-on-average.html
Season-ticket prices for
basketball’s  New York Knicks  will rise by an average 6.4 percent
next season, while prices for hockey’s Rangers will increase 4
percent.  The pricing was disclosed in a statement from Madison
Square Co., which owns the teams and arena. The company is in
the midst of a $1 billion renovation of the facility that is
scheduled to be completed next year.  Tickets for both teams will be offered at 26 undisclosed
price points, MSG said, adding that payment plans are available.  Knicks season tickets rose an average 4.9 percent this
season. Rangers tickets went up 9.5 percent.  The Knicks are 38-22, best in the Atlantic Division. The
Rangers are third in their division.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Soshnick in  New York  at 
 ssoshnick@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
